aiSLCAsync.name: aiSLCAsync
aiSLCAsync.contactinfo: Engineering MIB Administrator Postal: Applied Innovation Inc. 5800 Innovation Drive Dublin, Ohio 43017-3271 Tel: 614-798-2000 Fax: 614-798-1770 Email: snmp@aiinet.com
aiSLCAsync.description: MIB module for SLCs with asynchronous links.

aiSLCAsyncTable.name: aiSLCAsyncTable
aiSLCAsyncTable.description: Table of asynchronous link information indexed by link number. Includes link appplication and direct connect alias.

aislcasyLinkNumber.name: aislcasyLinkNumber
aislcasyLinkNumber.description: Link number to which this table row applies.

aislcasyApplication.name: aislcasyApplication
aislcasyApplication.description: Application configured for the this link. login(1): Link provides a login prompt. destination(2): Link is only a destination and cannot be used to place calls. directConnect(3): Link connects directly to the destination stored in aislcasyDirectConnectAlias. callMenu(4): Link provides a menu of destinations to which calls can be placed.

aislcasyDirectConnectAlias.name: aislcasyDirectConnectAlias
aislcasyDirectConnectAlias.description: Alias used when aislcasyApplication is directConnect(3). Maximum length is 255 characters.

aislcasyXonInterval.name: aislcasyXonInterval
aislcasyXonInterval.description: Time between sending successive XON characters. Maximum is 120 seconds. Zero disables sending periodic XONs.

aislcasyCallState.name: aislcasyCallState
aislcasyCallState.description: Read only string describing the current link call state.

aiSLCAsyncConnOptTable.name: aiSLCAsyncConnOptTable
aiSLCAsyncConnOptTable.description: Table of asynchronous link connect options indexed by link number. Includes settings for when and how to establish connections.

aislcacoLinkNumber.name: aislcacoLinkNumber
aislcacoLinkNumber.description: Link number to which this table row applies.

aislcacoOnActiveDSR.name: aislcacoOnActiveDSR
aislcacoOnActiveDSR.description: Consider link active when DSR is active.

aislcacoOnActiveDCD.name: aislcacoOnActiveDCD
aislcacoOnActiveDCD.description: Consider link active when DCD is active.

aislcacoOnIncomingChar.name: aislcacoOnIncomingChar
aislcacoOnIncomingChar.description: Consider link active when characters are received.

aislcacoDirectConnect.name: aislcacoDirectConnect
aislcacoDirectConnect.description: Connect to destination specified in aislcasyDirectConnectAlias as soon as the link is enabled. This overrides other connection options.

aislcacoRetryTimer.name: aislcacoRetryTimer
aislcacoRetryTimer.description: Wait interval after unsuccessful call. Maximum is 32767 seconds. Zero disables retry.

aislcacoConnectString.name: aislcacoConnectString
aislcacoConnectString.description: String to send immediately after a call is established. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aiSLCAsyncDiscOptTable.name: aiSLCAsyncDiscOptTable
aiSLCAsyncDiscOptTable.description: Table of asynchronous link disconnect options indexed by link number. Includes settings for when and how to close connections.

aislcadoLinkNumber.name: aislcadoLinkNumber
aislcadoLinkNumber.description: Link number to which this table row applies.

aislcadoOnLostDSR.name: aislcadoOnLostDSR
aislcadoOnLostDSR.description: Disconnect call when DSR is lost.

aislcadoOnLostDCD.name: aislcadoOnLostDCD
aislcadoOnLostDCD.description: Disconnect call when DCD is lost.

aislcadoOnBreak.name: aislcadoOnBreak
aislcadoOnBreak.description: Disconnect call when a break character is received.

aislcadoInactivityTimer.name: aislcadoInactivityTimer
aislcadoInactivityTimer.description: Interval of inactivity after which a call is disconnected. Maximum is 32767 seconds. Zero disables disconnect-on-inactivty.

aislcadoDisconnectString.name: aislcadoDisconnectString
aislcadoDisconnectString.description: String to send immediately before a call is disconnected. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcadoInactivityReceive.name: aislcadoInactivityReceive
aislcadoInactivityReceive.description: Inactivity Timer enabled when link receives calls.

aiSLCAsyncModemOptTable.name: aiSLCAsyncModemOptTable
aiSLCAsyncModemOptTable.description: Table of asynchronous link modem options indexed by link number. Includes settings for modem strings, dialing timeout, retry limit, and signal lead options.

aislcmdmLinkNumber.name: aislcmdmLinkNumber
aislcmdmLinkNumber.description: Link number to which this table row applies.

aislcmdmInitString.name: aislcmdmInitString
aislcmdmInitString.description: String to send when a link is enabled or restarted, possibly to place a modem in auto-answer mode, to cause a modem to dial a remote location, or to prepare a modem in some other way. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcmdmTermString.name: aislcmdmTermString
aislcmdmTermString.description: String to send immediately after the disconnect string, before a call is disconnected, possibly for the bennefit of an attached modem. Maximum length is 80 characters.

aislcmdmTimeToConnect.name: aislcmdmTimeToConnect
aislcmdmTimeToConnect.description: Number of seconds to wait for modem to connect after dialing. Maximum is 300 seconds. Minimum is 5 seconds

aislcmdmMaxDialAttempts.name: aislcmdmMaxDialAttempts
aislcmdmMaxDialAttempts.description: Maximum number of times to dial when placing an outgoing call. Maximum is 100 attempts. Zero retrys dialing forever.

aislcmdmDtrConnState.name: aislcmdmDtrConnState
aislcmdmDtrConnState.description: State of DTR when connected or connecting. on(1): DTR is on when link is connected or connecting. off(2): DTR is off when link is connected or connecting.

aislcmdmDtrDconnState.name: aislcmdmDtrDconnState
aislcmdmDtrDconnState.description: State of DTR when disconnected. on(1): DTR is on when link is disconnected. off(2): DTR is off when link is disconnected. toggle(3): DTR toggles on-to-off when link disconnects.

aislcmdmRtsConnState.name: aislcmdmRtsConnState
aislcmdmRtsConnState.description: State of DTR when connected or connecting. on(1), RTS is on when link is connected or connecting. off(2), RTS is off when link is connected or connecting. followsDSR(3), RTS follows the state of DSR when link is connected or connecting. xmitFlowControl(4), RTS is on when the DTE has data to send, and DTE sends only when DCE asserts CTS on. bidirectionalFlowControl(5) RTS is on when DTE is ready to accept data from DCE, and DTE sends only when DCE asserts CTS on followsData(6), RTS is asserted only when data is transmitted.

aislcmdmRtsDconnState.name: aislcmdmRtsDconnState
aislcmdmRtsDconnState.description: State of RTS when disconnected. on(1): RTS is on when link is disconnected. off(2): RTS is off when link is disconnected. toggle(3): DTR toggles on-to-off when link disconnects.
